      "content": "Even for a short period, such a massive dose carries risks that are hard to predict without lab work. While the body does excrete excess water-soluble vitamins, Vitamin D is fat-soluble, meaning it can accumulate in your body's tissues. Relying on anecdotal advice from forums instead of a healthcare professional is unsafe, as even temporary overloading can cause issues like kidney stress. Please prioritize a conversation with a doctor before taking such a high dose.",
